"<b>Oviferous</b>, ō-vif′ėr-us, <i>adj.</i> egg-bearing.—<i>n.</i> <b>O′vifer</b>, a small wire cage on a solid base, for carrying an egg safely. [L. <i>ovum</i>, an egg, <i>ferre</i>, to bear.]",
"<b>Oviform</b>, ō′vi-form, <i>adj.</i> having the form of an oval or egg. [L. <i>ovum</i>, an egg.]",
"<b>Oviform</b>, ō′vi-form, <i>adj.</i> like a sheep: ovine. [L. <i>ovis</i>, a sheep.]",
