"<b>Ovolo</b>, ō′vō-lō, <i>n.</i> (<i>archit.</i>) a moulding with the rounded part composed of a quarter of a circle, or of an arc of an ellipse with the curve greatest at the top. [It.,—L. <i>ovum</i>, an egg.]",
